summary: Pokemon GO: Mythical Pokemon Deoxys Arrives For EX Raid Battles
title: Pokemon GO: Mythical Pokemon Deoxys Arrives For EX Raid Battles
body:
Pokemon GO: Mythical Pokemon Deoxys Arrives For EX Raid Battles

Niantic is continuing to put a lot of effort in Pokemon GOand judging from user numbers and revenue it is continuing to pay off. The latest news is that Mythical Pokemon Deoxys from the Hoenn region will arrive for EX Raid Battles. The company says that while the Pokemon can prove a difficulty in battles, you get an EX Raid Pass, allowing you to bring a friend along. Here’s some details about…

blog.name: weirdandwackypokefusions
blog.title: Well that's strange!
blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Mightytales Mightyena and Ninetales fusion Dark/Fire Type Ability: Intimidate/Steakout Stats: HP - 78, Atk - 95, Def - 80, SpA -...
caption:
Mightytales

Mightyena and Ninetales fusion

Dark/Fire Type

Ability: Intimidate/Steakout

Stats: HP - 78, Atk - 95, Def - 80, SpA - 90, SpD - 80, Spe - 105

The Dark Fox Pokemon

Mightytales fluffs up and sticks up its many tails to make itself appear bigger to intimidate its opponent.  It will only obey a trainer if it see them as worthy of its trust. Many people say that it has dark and mysterious powers which it will use on an opponent that it deems strong enough for it to use them.

Request for @runaway-modblog. I hope you like it! Thank you for liking my fusions!

summary: (9/20/18) The Pokémon marathon on Twitch is now LIVE! The last 13 episodes that is going to be streamed (from Season 4 Johto...
body:
(9/20/18) The Pokémon marathon on Twitch is now LIVE!

The last 13 episodes that is going to be streamed (from Season 4 Johto League Champions) this week will feature a girl actually falling for Brock, Ash’s Chikorita evolving, a Pokémon balloon race, a glimpse of Generation III Pokémon, a showdown with Gym Leader Chuck, and much much more!

The episode set will rerun in multiple times today just so you won’t miss the stream depending on your schedule.

Watching with Twitch chat could be the best (or worst) experience you’ll ever have! But if you want a more comfy chat experience, feel free to talk/chat about the marathon in my Pokémon Discord server PokéTōku —> Invite link here :)
